reviews.review:
I've played almost 4 hours and I can tell that this game is not worth it.
I mean it really has the potential and it can be really fun but right now nope. Why?
-With the new update of the game the survivors can just play with the hunter jumping over windows, or fences that are placed one near another.. You don't stand a chance as a hunter if your pray is in that place;
-Constantly game blocking.. I can hear everything in the game, the game is still running and the survivors are still repairing the generators while my game just visually froze.. In the moment I pick up a survivor the game freezes (not always);
-If someone is lagging he/she is like a sonic on crack;
-The alt-f4 bug when the survivor is just quitting the game if he/she is losing and that game doesn't count..;
-Unfair placement of the ranks and levels.. If you're a starter you can't help it just to play against rank 1-10 and level 30 when you are rank 17-20 and level 1-5;

I refuse to play this game until the new update. I was tempted at 1-2 hours to request a refund but I gave it another chance. I hope everything is going to be fixed and when it does I'll play it and post a real review of finished game. :)

Gameplay is key, tense and fragile for the victims, a murder sandbox for the killer.
While the gameplay is pretty nice, i think it's worth mencioning these missing features. 

 - Co-op with friends (being worked on);
  - Proper matchmaking;
  - Controll settings;
  - Tutorial;
  - General perfomance stability;
  - Graphic settings.
